  Your new mantra (remember the '60s?) is, &quot;More water is good&quot;.  Just keep telling yourself, &quot;Fish live in water so more water is good&quot;.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  Trust Darrells' judgement in the matter. You know he is dead serious about improving our fisheries and from several decades of experience in fighting for minimum flow standards in the Southwest I can tell you that the fishing has improved everywhere it has been attained.<br>
   We all resist change. It is a natural human response, but stop a moment and remind yourself that you had no idea of what would work the first time you fished the Arkansas tailwaters yet you coped with it to the point of becoming a consummate professional. I'm sure you'll have far less trouble adapting to new water levels than we average part time fishermen.<br>
  In every instance that I have witnessed increases in minumum flow standards have resulted in more and bigger fish.<br>
  Darrell summed it up well with, &quot;---the important thing is to acquire the water reallocation.  We can't begin to improve anything without the flow mitigated first&quot;.<br>
  So I'll be writing my letters and posts and pushing for better standards in every way I can. To tell the truth I sorta like the thought of more and bigger fish. Gives an old fumbler like myself better odds. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#000000>(10/31/03 7:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Minimum Flow</span><hr size=1> Change the way you fish John.  CC is right.  More water equals more and better fish.  GET A BOAT.  The fish will move with the water and your Sight-Fishing-Wading -Areas will change a little but not that much.  THINK GRAVEL.....Water covers GRAVEL.   I know we disagree on this one but it is GOOD to cover more GRAVEL with water.  It's the same river but with a different twist.  I'm out there every day.  Fish tail water and the fish move differently.  GRAVEL....COVER GRAVEL.   Thats the Key man.  More Spawniing area...more bugs.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
