<br>
I don't want to seem like I am resisting change, or a nah-sayer, but this equates to a BIG change. We have been threatened for years with the closure of the Catch and Release areas. If they close the C&amp;R areas and institute consistantly higher water levels, fly fishing on the White and Norfork as we know it will be gone. If they (by they I mean the stake holders as described int the trout management plan) take the plan step by step and include &quot;all&quot; of the items described, we will have one of the greatest trout streams in the world. Hell, we already have the greatest trout stream in the world.<br>
<br>
